cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper focuses on studying the collective dynamics of a population of AI agents, which falls under the domain of multi-agent systems. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning to endow intelligence to the agents, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The study of collective behavior and emergent patterns in a population of agents can be related to social and information networks. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The use of deep reinforcement learning to train the agents can be categorized under machine learning. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The study of population dynamics and emergent behaviors can also be related to systems and control.
